<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>38<percent/> of 159</li> 
<li>2<percent/> of 1908</li> 
<li>100<percent/> of 61</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 100<percent/> of 61</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{100}\%\cdot{61}={61}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{38}\%\cdot{159}={60.42}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}\%\cdot{1908}={38.16}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 100<percent/> of 61 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>